Source: libmimic
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Nick Black <nick.black@sprezzatech.com>
XSBC-Original-Maintainer: Luciano Bello <luciano@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.9.4
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), cdbs, doxygen, libglib2.0-dev, python-all-dev, python-support, autotools-dev
XS-Python-Version: >= 2.4

Package: libmimic0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A video codec for Mimic V2.x content
 libmimic is an open source video decoding library for decoding Mimic V2.x-
 encoded content (fourCC: ML20), which is the encoding used by MSN Messenger
 for webcam conversations.

